A man has life-threatening injuries after he was involved in a lorry and car crash on the A38, police have said.Devon and Cornwall Police said it was called to Deep Lane in Plymouth at 20:05 GMT to reports of a crash between a blue Vauxhall Corsa and a lorry.Police said emergency services attended and part of the westbound carriageway was closed for five hours.The force said a 51-year-old man was taken to hospital. Officers are appealing for witnesses.
